rComments: Wow I know he's a terrible prof but mgfc20 is usually pretty easy. In the summer the midterm avg was almost an 80. This semester midterm avg 69, final 50. Very inconsistent in his teaching, just a terrible professor, he should stick with his admin role.

Bcs I have taken both fc10 and fc20 with Syed, his style of grading is clear. Midterm: 3/4 questions are from his previous exam, 1/4 is brand new and very difficult, if you are slightly capable you will recieve an 80%+ on midterm. MGFC20 group assignment is long, useless (more of a marketing assignment), and graded hard. Final is a 50% avg. Hard.

His lectures are the worst I've ever been to. He uses a lot of time to go through the simplest of examples and doesn't even go through the more difficult stuff in class but still expects everyone to know the stuff in the exam. Grading totally random. You might get points deducted for correct answers and even his own solutions are partly wrong.

In FD10: legendary" teacher I have ever seen on any of these finance courses at utsc. No question for practice was posted after midterm. Course syllabus was a nonsense since Syed seldom followed it and I even could not do self-learning. In the last class before the final, he invite someone talking about companies unrelated to course material. Ehhh

I've taken 2 courses with Ahmed, and I think that he is past it as a professor. He is very unclear, disorganized and generally makes going to class a torture. The difference in teaching ability between Ahmed and the other Finance profs at UTSC are night and day. He is a very nice person, maybe he should just stick with his administrative role.
don't take FD10 with this teacher! This teacher has a horrible accent and handwriting. Most time in class he talks stories of nonsense and I have no idea on what I am learning in class.

Worst teaching style out of all Finance profs at UTSC. Test questions are not great, as you can get a really high mark by simply writing down that specific question on your crib sheet. If you don't have that question, be prepared to lose at least half of your marks. Took 7 Finance courses at UTSC, Ahmed has by far the worst teaching ability.

Makes the midterm super easy then really screws you on the final. His exam questions are super long and is almost impossible to finish with the time given. He even admits it to the class. My mark dropped 10% after the final exam. Don't recommend.

Releases final marks on day he goes on vacation for 2 weeks... Class act. Never answered questions. Was rude and couldn't care less. Would use obscure questions on midterm/final from practice questions and practice tests. If you had the specific question on your crib sheet youll get the question, otherwise good luck. Most infuriating professor

I don't know what's wrong with today's students. They complaint about exams being hard. But a REAL university is supposed to challenge your cognitive ability to see if you're smart enough to deal with ABSTRACT concepts, working hard enough to be there to get a degree. Being hard is a given, being easy to get marks is bad for your academic health.
Literally the worst prof in the world- rude, unhelpful and doesn't teach well at all. Avoid at all costs
Didnt learn anything in his class, not a good professor. Just do the past finals, and hope those similar questions come in the exam.
